    "auto_merge": {
        "commit_message": "and deduplicate some stuff.\n\n1. Factor out `_PyType_Lookup`/`__Pyx_PyObject_GetAttrStr` (depending on compilation options)\n   into a separate function, since it's pretty repetitive.\n2. Handle the possibility that `__Pyx_setup_reduce_is_named` can fail with an exception\n   that we shouldn't ignore.\n3. Handle the possibility that looking up `__setstate__` can fail with an exception\n   that we shouldn't ignore",
        "commit_title": "Improve error handling when setting up reduce functions (GH-7613)",
